Marvin Goldstein was named president of the retailer's Dayton Hudson Department Store unit.
Mr. Goldstein, 46 years old, was formerly executive vice president, merchandising, at the unit.
The president's post he assumes has been vacant for about a year.
Mr. Goldstein will report to Stephen E. Watson, 44, who was last week named to the post of executive vice president at the parent, but retains his posts as chairman and chief executive officer of the department-store unit. 

